## Github Action Rules

- Check if `package.json` exists in project root and summarize key scripts
- Check if `.nvmrc` exists in project root
- Check if `.env.example` exists in project root to identify key `env:` variables
- Always use `git branch -a | cat` to verify whether we use `main` or `master` branch
- Always use `env:` variables and secrets attached to jobs instead of global workflows
- Always use `npm ci` for Node-based dependency setup
- Extract common steps into composite actions in separate files
- Once you're done, as a final step conduct the following: 

1) For each public action always use <tool>"Run Terminal"</tool> to see what is the most up-to-date version (use only major version):

```bash
curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/{owner}/{repo}/releases/latest | grep '"tag_name":' | sed -E 's/.*"v([0-9]+).*/\1/'
```

2) (Ask if needed) Use <tool>"Run Terminal"</tool> to fetch README.md and see if we're not using any deprecated actions by mistake:

```bash
curl -s https://raw.githubusercontent.com/{owner}/{repo}/refs/tags/v{TAG_VERSION}/README.md
```

3) (Ask if needed) Use <tool>"Run Terminal"</tool> to fetch repo metadata and see if we're not using any deprecated actions by mistake:

```bash
curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/{owner}/{repo} | grep '"archived":'
```

4) (Ask if needed) In case of linter issues related to action parameters, try to fetch action description directly from GitHub and use the following command:

```bash
curl -s https://raw.githubusercontent.com/{owner}/{repo}/refs/heads/{main/master}/action.yml
```

### Cloudflare Pages deployment (optional)

- Prefer a separate, optional job gated by required secrets/vars:
  - **secrets.CF_API_TOKEN**: Cloudflare API Token (Pages Write, Account Read)
  - **secrets.CF_ACCOUNT_ID**: Cloudflare Account ID
  - **vars.CF_PAGES_PROJECT_NAME**: Cloudflare Pages project name
- Build with Astro Cloudflare adapter by setting `ASTRO_ADAPTER=cloudflare` for that job only.
- Use `cloudflare/wrangler-action@v3` (NOT deprecated `pages-action`) with command `pages deploy ./dist --project-name=${{ vars.CF_PAGES_PROJECT_NAME }}`.
- Keep CI stages: format → lint → test → build; run deploy after tests.
- For manual deployment, use `workflow_dispatch` trigger and check `github.event_name == 'workflow_dispatch'` in job condition.

Example job gate:

```yaml
if: ${{ github.event_name == 'workflow_dispatch' && secrets.CF_API_TOKEN && secrets.CF_ACCOUNT_ID && vars.CF_PAGES_PROJECT_NAME }}
```

Example deployment step:

```yaml
- name: Deploy to Cloudflare Pages
  uses: cloudflare/wrangler-action@v3
  with:
    apiToken: ${{ secrets.CF_API_TOKEN }}
    accountId: ${{ secrets.CF_ACCOUNT_ID }}
    command: pages deploy ./dist --project-name=${{ vars.CF_PAGES_PROJECT_NAME }}
```

Latest major version discovery for Wrangler action:

```bash
curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/cloudflare/wrangler-action/releases/latest | grep '"tag_name":' | sed -E 's/.*"v([0-9]+).*/\1/'
```